Hi, I'm a 23 years old female.
I have gained a lot of weight in the last year, although I didn't really change my diet.
I also struggle with depression and anxiety.
Recently I took a blood test, and my TSH level is at 5,06.
My doctor said that was strange and could mean I have a condition in my thyroid, like hypothyroidism.
I am going to take another blood test, one more specific, but right now I'm really worried and hope you can help me.
I have always hated my body but only now I can see that I was actually pretty normal back then. I feel miserable with this extra weight that doesn't seem to go away. I've heard it's impossible to lose weight if you have hypothyroidism. 
Is this true? Is there a way to effectively treat hypothyroidism? Are the success rates high? 
Thank you so much
